CHANGELOG.md
     1→# Changelog
     2→
     3→All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.
    11→## [14.0.3] (2026-01-31)
    12→
    13→### Added
    14→
    15→- Release Policy document ([#2462])
    17→### Changes
    18→
    19→- old major versions now supported for 12 months instead of just previous major version, to give predictable end-of-life date ([#2462])
    20→- clarify typing for deprecated callback parameter to `.outputHelp()` ([#2427])
    21→- simple readability improvements to README ([#2465])
    23→## [14.0.2] (2025-10-25)
    24→
    25→### Changed
    26→
    27→- improve negative number auto-detection test ([#2428])
    28→- update (dev) dependencies
    30→## [14.0.1] (2025-09-12)
    31→
    32→### Fixed
    33→
    34→- broken markdown link in README ([#2369])
    36→### Changed
    37→
    38→- improve code readability by using optional chaining ([#2394])
    39→- use more idiomatic code with object spread instead of `Object.assign()` ([#2395])
    40→- improve code readability using `string.endsWith()` instead of `string.slice()` ([#2396])
    41→- refactor `.parseOptions()` to process args array in-place ([#2409])
    42→- change private variadic support routines from `._concatValue()` to `._collectValue()` (change code from `array.concat()` to `array.push()`) ([#2410])
    43→- update (dev) dependencies
    45→## [14.0.0] (2025-05-18)
    46→
    47→### Added
    48→
    49→- support for groups of options and commands in the help using low-level `.helpGroup()` on `Option` and `Command`, and higher-level `.optionsGroup()` and `.commandsGroup()` which can be used in chaining way to specify group title for following options/commands ([#2328])
    50→- support for unescaped negative numbers as option-arguments and command-arguments ([#2339])
    51→- TypeScript: add `parseArg` property to `Argument` class ([#2359])
    53→### Fixed
    54→
    55→- remove bogus leading space in help when option has default value but not a description ([#2348])
    56→- `.configureOutput()` now makes copy of settings instead of modifying in-place, fixing side-effects ([#2350])
    58→### Changed
    59→
    60→- *Breaking:* Commander 14 requires Node.js v20 or higher
    61→- internal refactor of `Help` class adding `.formatItemList()` and `.groupItems()` methods ([#2328])
    63→## [13.1.0] (2025-01-21)
    64→
    65→### Added
    66→
    67→- support a pair of long option flags to allow a memorable shortened flag, like `.option('--ws, --workspace')` ([#2312])
    69→## [13.0.0] (2024-12-30)
    70→
    71→### Added
    72→
    73→- support multiple calls to `.parse()` with default settings ([#2299])
    74→- add `.saveStateBeforeParse()` and `.restoreStateBeforeParse()` for use by subclasses ([#2299])
    75→- style routines like `styleTitle()` to add color to help using `.configureHelp()` or Help subclass ([#2251])
    76→- color related support in `.configureOutput()` for `getOutHasColors()`, `getErrHasColors()`, and `stripColor()` ([#2251])
    77→- Help property for `minWidthToWrap` ([#2251])
    78→- Help methods for `displayWidth()`, `boxWrap()`, `preformatted()` et al ([#2251])
    80→### Changed
    81→
    82→- *Breaking*: excess command-arguments cause an error by default, see migration tips ([#2223])
    83→- *Breaking*: throw during Option construction for unsupported option flags, like multiple characters after single `-` ([#2270])
    84→  - note: support for dual long option flags added in Commander 13.1
    85→- *Breaking*: throw on multiple calls to `.parse()` if `storeOptionsAsProperties: true` ([#2299])
    86→- TypeScript: include implicit `this` in parameters for action handler callback ([#2197])
    88→### Deleted
    89→
    90→- *Breaking*: `Help.wrap()` refactored into `formatItem()` and `boxWrap()` ([#2251])
    92→### Migration Tips
    93→
    94→**Excess command-arguments**
   156→## [13.0.0-0] (2024-12-07)
