   160→## [12.1.0] (2024-05-18)
   161→
   162→### Added
   163→
   164→- auto-detect special node flags `node --eval` and `node --print` when call `.parse()` with no arguments ([#2164])
   166→### Changed
   167→
   168→- prefix require of Node.js core modules with `node:` ([#2170])
   169→- format source files with Prettier ([#2180])
   170→- switch from StandardJS to directly calling ESLint for linting ([#2153])
   171→- extend security support for previous major version of Commander ([#2150])
   173→### Removed
   174→
   175→- removed unimplemented Option.fullDescription from TypeScript definition ([#2191])
   177→## [12.0.0] (2024-02-03)
   178→
   179→### Added
   180→
   181→- `.addHelpOption()` as another way of configuring built-in help option ([#2006])
   182→- `.helpCommand()` for configuring built-in help command ([#2087])
   184→### Fixed
   185→
   186→- *Breaking:* use non-zero exit code when spawned executable subcommand terminates due to a signal ([#2023])
   187→- *Breaking:* check `passThroughOptions` constraints when using `.addCommand` and throw if parent command does not have `.enablePositionalOptions()` enabled ([#1937])
   189→### Changed
   190→
   191→- *Breaking:* Commander 12 requires Node.js v18 or higher ([#2027])
   192→- *Breaking:* throw an error if add an option with a flag which is already in use ([#2055])
   193→- *Breaking:* throw an error if add a command with name or alias which is already in use ([#2059])
   194→- *Breaking:* throw error when calling `.storeOptionsAsProperties()` after setting an option value ([#1928])
   195→- replace non-standard JSDoc of `@api private` with documented `@private` ([#1949])
   196→- `.addHelpCommand()` now takes a Command (passing string or boolean still works as before but deprecated) ([#2087])
   197→- refactor internal implementation of built-in help option ([#2006])
   198→- refactor internal implementation of built-in help command ([#2087])
   200→### Deprecated
   201→
   202→- `.addHelpCommand()` passing string or boolean (use `.helpCommand()` or pass a Command) ([#2087])
   204→### Removed
   205→
   206→- *Breaking:* removed default export of a global Command instance from CommonJS (use the named `program` export instead) ([#2017])
   208→### Migration Tips
   209→
   210→**global program**
