   431→## [8.1.0] (2021-07-27)
   432→
   433→### Added
   434→
   435→- `.copyInheritedSettings()` ([#1557])
   436→- update Chinese translations of documentation for Commander v8 ([#1570])
   437→- `Argument` methods for `.argRequired()` and `.argOptional()` ([#1567])
   439→## [8.0.0] (2021-06-25)
   440→
   441→### Added
   442→
   443→- `.argument(name, description)` for adding command-arguments ([#1490])
   444→  - supports default value for optional command-arguments ([#1508])
   445→  - supports custom processing function ([#1508])
   446→- `.createArgument()` factory method ([#1497])
   447→- `.addArgument()` ([#1490])
   448→- `Argument` supports `.choices()` ([#1525])
   449→- `.showHelpAfterError()` to display full help or a custom message after an error ([#1534])
   450→- `.hook()` with support for `'preAction'` and `'postAction'` callbacks ([#1514])
   451→- client typing of `.opts()` return type using TypeScript generics ([#1539])
   452→- the number of command-arguments is checked for programs without an action handler ([#1502])
   453→- `.getOptionValue()` and `.setOptionValue()` ([#1521])
   455→### Changed
   456→
   457→- refactor and simplify TypeScript declarations (with no default export) ([#1520])
   458→- `.parseAsync()` is now declared as `async` ([#1513])
   459→- *Breaking:* `Help` method `.visibleArguments()` returns array of `Argument` ([#1490])
   460→- *Breaking:* Commander 8 requires Node.js 12 or higher ([#1500])
   461→- *Breaking:* `CommanderError` code `commander.invalidOptionArgument` renamed `commander.invalidArgument` ([#1508])
   462→- *Breaking:* TypeScript declaration for `.addTextHelp()` callback no longer allows result of `undefined`, now just `string` ([#1516])
   463→- refactor `index.tab` into a file per class ([#1522])
   464→- remove help suggestion from "unknown command" error message (see `.showHelpAfterError()`) ([#1534])
   465→- `Command` property `.arg` initialised to empty array (was previously undefined) ([#1529])
   466→- update dependencies
   468→### Deprecated
   469→
   470→- second parameter of `cmd.description(desc, argDescriptions)` for adding argument descriptions ([#1490])
   471→  - (use new `.argument(name, description)` instead)
   472→- `InvalidOptionArgumentError` (replaced by `InvalidArgumentError`) ([#1508])
   474→### Removed
   475→
   476→- *Breaking:* TypeScript declaration for default export of global `Command` object ([#1520])
   477→  - (still available as named `program` export)
   479→### Migration Tips
   480→
   481→If you have a simple program without an action handler, you will now get an error if
   482→there are missing command-arguments.
