   522→## [7.2.0] (2021-03-22)
   523→
   524→### Added
   525→
   526→- TypeScript typing for `parent` property on `Command` ([#1475])
   527→- TypeScript typing for `.attributeName()` on `Option` ([#1483])
   528→- support information in package ([#1477])
   530→### Changed
   531→
   532→- improvements to error messages, README, and tests
   533→- update dependencies
   535→## [7.1.0] (2021-02-15)
   536→
   537→### Added
   538→
   539→- support for named imports from ECMAScript modules ([#1440])
   540→- add `.cjs` to list of expected script file extensions ([#1449])
   541→- allow using option choices and variadic together ([#1454])
   543→### Fixed
   544→
   545→- replace use of deprecated `process.mainModule` ([#1448])
   546→- regression for legacy `command('*')` and call when command line includes options ([#1464])
   547→- regression for `on('command:*', ...)` and call when command line includes unknown options ([#1464])
   548→- display best error for combination of unknown command and unknown option (i.e. unknown command) ([#1464])
   550→### Changed
   551→
   552→- make TypeScript typings tests stricter ([#1453])
   553→- improvements to README and tests
   555→## [7.0.0] (2021-01-15)
   556→
   557→### Added
   558→
   559→- `.enablePositionalOptions()` to let program and subcommand reuse same option ([#1427])
   560→- `.passThroughOptions()` to pass options through to other programs without needing `--` ([#1427])
   561→- `.allowExcessArguments(false)` to show an error message if there are too many command-arguments on command line for the action handler ([#1409])
   562→- `.configureOutput()` to modify use of stdout and stderr or customise display of errors ([#1387])
   563→- use `.addHelpText()` to add text before or after the built-in help, for just current command or also for all subcommands ([#1296])
   564→- enhance Option class ([#1331])
   565→  - allow hiding options from help
   566→  - allow restricting option arguments to a list of choices
   567→  - allow setting how default value is shown in help
   568→- `.createOption()` to support subclassing of automatically created options (like `.createCommand()`) ([#1380])
   569→- refactor the code generating the help into a separate public Help class ([#1365])
   570→  - support sorting subcommands and options in help
   571→  - support specifying wrap width (columns)
   572→  - allow subclassing Help class
   573→  - allow configuring Help class without subclassing
   575→### Changed
   576→
   577→- *Breaking:* options are stored safely by default, not as properties on the command ([#1409])
   578→  - this especially affects accessing options on program, use `program.opts()`
   579→  - revert behaviour with `.storeOptionsAsProperties()`
   580→- *Breaking:* action handlers are passed options and command separately ([#1409])
   581→- deprecated callback parameter to `.help()` and `.outputHelp()` (removed from README) ([#1296])
   582→- *Breaking:* errors now displayed using `process.stderr.write()` instead of `console.error()`
   583→- deprecate `.on('--help')` (removed from README) ([#1296])
   584→- initialise the command description to empty string (previously undefined) ([#1365])
   585→- document and annotate deprecated routines ([#1349])
   587→### Fixed
   588→
   589→- wrapping bugs in help ([#1365])
   590→  - first line of command description was wrapping two characters early
   591→  - pad width calculation was not including help option and help command
   592→  - pad width calculation was including hidden options and commands
   593→- improve backwards compatibility for custom command event listeners ([#1403])
   595→### Deleted
   596→
   597→- *Breaking:* `.passCommandToAction()` ([#1409])
   598→  - no longer needed as action handler is passed options and command
   599→- *Breaking:* "extra arguments" parameter to action handler ([#1409])
   600→  - if being used to detect excess arguments, there is now an error available by setting `.allowExcessArguments(false)`
   602→### Migration Tips
   603→
   604→The biggest change is the parsed option values. Previously the options were stored by default as properties on the command object, and now the options are stored separately.
